he irrational, and a critique of materialism and positivism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFuturism (Literary movement). 0aFuturism (Music). 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Composers & Musicians.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095156340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520951563423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520951563/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles